Soviet industrial output in the firstquarter of this year grew by 2.5 pct compared with the firstthree months of 1986, Tass news agency reported.    A regular meeting of the Politburo heard that in March,industry achieved the average daily rate needed to fulfilannual targets.    Quarterly plans were exceeded in the fuel and power sectorand agriculture, where output grew by 8.7 pct compared with thesame period last year, it said. Plans were not fulfilled by theengineering and building ministries, the chemical and timbersectors, rail transport and light industry, it added. Reuter&#3;